Meet our Dance Instructors!
Cassidy
Cassidy
Cassidy
Originally from Eastern Kentucky, Cass has been line dancing and teaching for three years, as well as dancing country swing for two. She has experience teaching locally at Three Daughters Brewing, The Kangaroo, and many more! Cass has a passion for Line Dancing and loves sharing it with others!  Dance with Cass on Tuesdays from  7 - 9pm.
Kate
Cassidy
Cassidy
Kate, originally from Long Island, NY, is passionate about line dancing and has been doing it for 8 years. She also enjoys 2 step, progressive partner, and is learning Country Swing. Kate loves teaching dance and believes it's all about having fun and enjoying the experience.
Dance with Kate on Wednesdays & Fridays from  7 - 9pm.
Brandon
Cassidy
Brandon
Brandon discovered his love for line dancing in 2018 and started teaching it in 2021. He has a burning passion for it and strives to pass on the joy of line dancing to all his students. Brandon approaches every lesson with the hope of encouraging his students to take the leap of faith and embrace this beautiful art form.
Dance with Brandon on Thursdays from  7 - 9pm.
